HEADWORD: Breastrail
<hw>Breast"rail`</hw> <pr>(-r⟦amac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
upper rail of any parapet of ordinary height, as of a balcony; the
railing of a quarter-deck, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

